com.metreeca.tray.sys

Class Cache

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.metreeca.tray.sys.Cache

  • public final class Cache
extends Object
    URL cache.

    Retrieves and caches remote URL content, delegating storage to a backing blob store.

      • Cache

        public Cache()
        Creates a new URL cache.

        The new cache is configured with default handlers for file: and http(s): URL schemas.

    • Method Detail

      • cache

        public static Supplier<Cache> cache()
        Retrieves the default cache factory.
        Returns:
        the default cache factory, which creates a vanilla cache with no customization

      • fetcher

        public Cache fetcher(String schema,
                     BiConsumer<URL,Store.Blob> fetcher)
        Registers a custom URL fetcher.

        Fetchers are expected to test for themselves the caching status of the target URL, calling for instance Store.Blob.exists() and checking other relevant metadata.

        Parameters:
        schema - the URL schema the custom fetcher will be applied to
        fetcher - the custom fetcher that will be used to retrieve content from URLs with schema
        Returns:
        this cache
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if either schema or fetcher is null

      • store

        public Cache store(Store store)
        Configures the backing blob store for this cache.

        Defaults to a blob store storing content to the "cache" storage area located by the current storage tool.

        Parameters:
        store - the backing blob store for this cache
        Returns:
        this cache
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if store is null

      • exec

        public <V> V exec(URL url,
                  Function<Store.Blob,V> task)
           throws UncheckedIOException
        Executes a task on the content retrieved from a URL.
        Type Parameters:
        V - the type of the value returned by task
        Parameters:
        url - the URL content is to be retrieved from
        task - the task to be executed on the contents retrieved from url; takes as argument a store blob providing access to the (possibly cached) content retrieved from url using the registered URL fetcher for its URL schema or an empty blob, if no suitable fetcher is registered
        Returns:
        the value returned by task when applied to the contents retrieved from url
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if either url or task is null or task returns a null value
        UncheckedIOException - if an I/O error occurred while retrieving content from url

      • exec

        public <V> V exec(URL url,
                  BiConsumer<URL,Store.Blob> fetcher,
                  Function<Store.Blob,V> task)
           throws UncheckedIOException
        Executes a task on the content retrieved from a URL using a specific fetcher.
        Type Parameters:
        V - the type of the value returned by task
        Parameters:
        url - the URL content is to be retrieved from
        fetcher - the URL fetcherf to be used for retrieving content from url
        task - the task to be executed on the contents retrieved from url using fetcher; takes as argument a store blob providing access to the (possibly cached) content retrieved from url using fetcher
        Returns:
        the value returned by task when applied to the contents retrieved from url
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any of url, fetcher or task is null or task returns a null value
        UncheckedIOException - if an I/O error occurred while retrieving content from url
